Business Brief -- Spar Aerospace Ltd.:
   Firm Gets NASA Contract
   Totaling $55.9 Million
Spar, based in Brampton, Ontario, designed, developed and
built the Canadarm under contract to the Canadian government.
The first Canadarm was delivered to NASA in 1981 and
follow-on contracts to support it have generated more than
C$200 million in revenue.
   Spar is a maker of satellites and related products.